'''Ejnar Sylvest''' (1880 – 1972) was a Danish family physician who described [[Bornholm disease]] or the "devil's grip" following an outbreak affecting 23 fisherman in [[Melstedgård]] and [[Gudhjem]] whilst on holiday on [[Bornholm Island]], Denamrk.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://litfl.com/ejner-sylvest/|title=Ejner Sylvest • LITFL Medical Blog • Medical Eponym Library|last=|first=|date=3 August 2018|work=Life in the Fast Lane|access-date=2 December 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Pickles|first=William N.|date=17 June 1954|title=Sylvest's Disease (Bornholm Disease)|url=https://www.nejm.org/doi/pdf/10.1056/NEJM195406172502405|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|language=en|volume=250|issue=24|pages=1033–1036|doi=10.1056/nejm195406172502405|issn=0028-4793|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=z44JDgAAQBAJ&pg=PA88&dq=Ejnar+Sylvest&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjGia6lsoHfAhVSRxUIHR-jAKEQ6AEIMDAC#v=onepage&q=Ejnar%20Sylvest&f=false|title=The Amazing Language of Medicine: Understanding Medical Terms and Their Backstories|last=Taylor|first=Robert B.|date=2017|publisher=Springer|year=|isbn=9783319503288|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/32886500_Making_the_human_body_transparent_the_impact_of_NMR_and_MRI_Research_in_general_practice_Drugs_in_psychiatric_practice_The_MRC_Common_Cold_Unit|title=Making the human body transparent: the impact of NMR and MRI; Research in general practice; Drugs in psychiatric practice; The MRC Common Cold Unit|last=Tansey|first=Tilli|last2=Christie|first2=D|last3=Reynolds|first3=L|date=11 January 1998|publisher=Wellcome Trust|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>
