{{Infobox Hospital | Name = Murambinda Mission Hospital | Org/Group = | Image = <!-- optional --> | Caption = <!-- optional --> | Logo = | Location = [[Murambinda]] | Region = [[Buhera District]] | State = [[Manicaland Province]] | Country = {{flag|Zimbabwe}} | HealthCare = [[Community hospital|Community Hospital]] | Type = General | Specialty = | Standards = <!-- optional if no national standards --> | Emergency = | Affiliation= | Beds = 200 | Founded = 1968 | Closed = <!-- optional --> | Website = [http://www.fmh.org.uk/FMH06-07.pdf Homepage] | Wiki-Links = [[List of hospitals in Zimbabwe]] |}}
'''Murambinda Mission Hospital''' (MMH), is a hospital in [[Zimbabwe]]. The hospital, also known as '''Murambinda Hospital''', is located in the town of [[Murambinda]], [[Buhera District]], [[Manicaland Province]], in eastern Zimbabwe. Its location is approximately {{convert|30|km|0}}, by road, northeast of the village of [[Buhera]], where the district headquarters are located.<ref>[http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Zimbabwe_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Buhera%20()%20&toplace=Murambinda%20Business%20Centre%20()&fromlat=-19.3333333&tolat=-19.2666667&fromlng=31.4333333&tolng=31.65 Map Showing Buhera And Murambinda With Distance Marker]</ref> This location lies approximately {{convert|140|km|0}}, by road, southwest of the city of [[Mutare]] (pop:184,205),<ref>[http://www.wolframalpha.com/entities/cities_population/what_is_the_population_of_mutare,_zimbabwe%3F/gj/re/zo/ Estimated Population of Mutare In 2004]</ref> the location of the provincial headquarters.<ref>[http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Zimbabwe_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Mutare%20()%20&toplace=Murambinda%20Business%20Centre%20()&fromlat=-18.9666667&tolat=-19.2666667&fromlng=32.6666667&tolng=31.65 Road Distance Between Mutare And Murambinda With Map]</ref>
==Overview== The hospital is a rural community hospital,under [[Ministry of Health]] owned and administered by the Sisters of the Little Company of Mary, under the endorsement and supervision of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Harare.It is administered by the Ministry of Health.<ref>[http://www.mohcw.gov.zw/index.php/health-system-delivery.]</ref> A school of nursing that is affiliated and sits adjacent to the hospital is owned and administered by the same organization, under similar arrangements with the [[Roman Catholic Church]] and the government of Zimbabwe. The hospital has 200 beds and is the only hospital in Buhera District, with a population of nearly 300,000 over an area with a radius of about {{convert|100|km|mi}}. The professional staff at the hospital includes: 4 [[physician]]s/[[surgeon]]s, and a number of [[nurses]] and [[midwives]].<ref>[http://www.fmh.org.uk/FMH06-07.pdf Overview of Buhera District] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081121215529/http://www.fmh.org.uk/FMH06-07.pdf |date=2008-11-21 }}</ref>
==History== The hospital was established in 1968, by the [[Sisters of the Little Company of Mary]], under the auspices of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Harare]]. Technically the [[Government of Zimbabwe]] is expected to provide subsidies and financial assistance, although sometimes that assistance never comes.
'''Friends of Murambinda Hospital''' (FMH), a [[United Kingdom]]-registered [[non government organization|NGO]], assists in recruiting volunteer healthcare professionals and medical students to work on volunteer, part-time or full-time basis at the hospital.
