{{main|Immunology}}
'''Veterinary immunology''' is the study of all aspects of [[immune system]] in animals. It is a branch under [[Biomedical sciences|biomedical science]] and related to [[zoology]] and [[veterinary science]]s. Interests include malfunctions and disorders, but also health, of the immune system in animals. It is interested in how the immune system works, how vaccines prevent disease and why vaccines sometimes do not work and cause adverse reactions.

